                                <p>The Ludum Dare challenge is simple: a theme chosen and once its revealed, you have 72 hours to create a game for submission and review by the rest of the community.  Ludum Dare #41 was our first official game jam and we had a blast.  The theme chosen was "combine two incompatible genres" and we did the most outlandish thing we could think of- combine a first person shooter with golf.  And we really combined everything.  The drama and grittiness of an FPS is all over the menu and overall styling of the game but the golf courses are low poly, brightly colored, and downright cute.  Most importantly, even the mechanics are combined- you shoot the ball into the hole with a variety of high powered weapons.</p>
